      "patch": "@@ -2,23 +2,32 @@\n <rss xmlns:sparkle=\"http://www.andymatuschak.org/xml-namespaces/sparkle\" version=\"2.0\">\n     <channel>\n         <item>\n-            <title>0.7.0</title>\n-            <pubDate>Tue, 30 Dec 2025 03:43:38 +0100</pubDate>\n+            <title>0.8.0</title>\n+            <pubDate>Mon, 19 Jan 2026 08:31:41 +0000</pubDate>\n             <link>https://raw.githubusercontent.com/steipete/Trimmy/main/appcast.xml</link>\n-            <sparkle:version>27</sparkle:version>\n-            <sparkle:shortVersionString>0.7.0</sparkle:shortVersionString>\n+            <sparkle:version>28</sparkle:version>\n+            <sparkle:shortVersionString>0.8.0</sparkle:shortVersionString>\n             <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>15.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>\n-            <description><![CDATA[<h2>Trimmy 0.7.0</h2>\n+            <description><![CDATA[<h2>Trimmy 0.8.0</h2>\n <ul>\n-<li><strong>Highlight:</strong> Context-aware trimming with terminal detection, plus per-terminal aggressiveness (Cmd-C tracking + frontmost-app fallback).</li>\n-<li>Terminal detection now covers Ghostty, WezTerm, Alacritty, Hyper, and Warp Stable bundle IDs for context-aware trimming.</li>\n-<li>Aggressiveness now splits between general apps and terminals (defaults: Low + Normal), plus a \u201cNone\u201d option to disable auto-trim in regular apps.</li>\n-<li>Settings: added Advanced tab and moved CLI installer, debug tools, and clipboard fallbacks there.</li>\n-<li>Menu bar icon now animates whenever a trim happens.</li>\n+<li>Added a menu-only \u201cPaste Reformatted Markdown\u201d action to join wrapped markdown paragraphs and bullet lists while preserving blank lines and fenced code blocks.</li>\n+<li>Path quoting now only wraps standalone paths (not commands or sentences) when they contain spaces (#17, thanks @n0an).</li>\n </ul>\n <p><a href=\"https://github.com/steipete/Trimmy/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md\">View full changelog</a></p>\n ]]></description>\n-      